From which parts of the world do you move?
Last year, the Police and Border Guard Board (PPA) extended and issued a record number of over 13,000 residence permits to third-country nationals who have mostly travelled to Estonia for work, study or family.
For example, last year, it was decided to issue a temporary residence permit to 6,702 aliens, but this number was 4,928 last year.
The authorities cannot say how many immigrants will eventually stay permanently in Estonia, but such an analysis is being prepared by the Ministry of the Interior.
While nearly 500 Ukrainians moved to Estonia a year a decade ago, in recent years the number is approaching 2000.
The number of applicants for a residence permit increased dramatically during the crisis in Ukraine – in 2014, 1,087 people received a temporary residence permit, compared to 675 the year before.
According to Statistics Estonia, the number of Ukrainian citizens is growing the most in Estonia – last year, 850 more Ukrainian citizens arrived in Estonia than left.
"The Ukrainian community has always been large in Estonia, and because of the complicated circumstances in the country, it is natural that people look for work and opportunities to study in a country where the community and many families are already ahead of them," Kristin Rammus, a spokesman for the Ministry of the Interior, said.
Last year and last year, the number of Ukrainians who have been granted temporary residence permits was even higher than the number of Russian citizens, although in ten years the number of temporary residence permits issued to the latter has been the highest.
While Ukrainians mostly come here to work, Russian citizens do so for the sake of family migration.
"Given the historical Russian community here, they are more likely to have the largest family connections with people living in Russia," said Helina Maasing, a migration researcher at the Estonian Academy of Security Sciences.
“If you look at where Russian citizens who have been granted Estonian residence permits have moved to, then Ida-Viru County is immediately after Harju County,” he added, pointing out that about 40 per cent of them have married a citizen of the European Union.
Last year, 1,696 Russian citizens received a temporary residence permit, which is also a record number.
At the same time, the number of Russians who wanted to renew their residence permit decreased.
"The reason for the hype is that a new residence permit for settling permanently in Estonia has been applied for instead of the extension of the residence permit," Rammus, a spokesman for the Ministry of the Interior, said.
Foreigners who have lived here for at least three years can apply for a new residence permit for settling permanently in Estonia from the previous year.
Its purpose is to encourage people who have adapted to stay here.
A residence permit for long-term residents, for example, requires five years.
Due to the new residence permit, the extension of the old residence permit has probably also decreased.
For example, last year, 146 Ukrainians who have worked here for at least three years were granted such a residence permit.
Now the Ukrainians can change jobs and the Estonian state will no longer keep its finger on whether the salary criterion is met.
This residence permit became popular – last year the applicants were the holders of grey passports (1029), Russians (487), Indians (54) and Nigerians (36).
A total of 1968 people received a residence permit for settling in Estonia, including 23 Americans, 12 Egyptians, 18 Georgians and the same number of Chinese.
In the first half of this year, the total number of such applicants is already 1269.
In ten years, Nigeria has surprisingly become one of the most active applicants for Estonian residence permits.
In 2007, three residence permits were issued to Nigerians, compared to 200 last year.
Students come from Nigeria to study at universities.
Estonian institutions of higher education are also popular among Georgians, Chinese and Turks, for example.
The number of citizens of India, Bangladesh and Nigeria has increased mainly due to educational migration.
For them, too, the rule is that where a community has emerged in advance, it will be easier for others to come along,” Rammus added.
