They spoke to The Associated Press on condition that their anonymity be guaranteed as they were not allowed to discuss the PSG situation.
The latest published reports show that PSG made profits of more than EUR 10 million in the 2015-2016 season, with a turnover of around EUR 542.4 million.
Data for the last financial year have not yet been published.
PSG hopes Neymar’s arrival will have a positive impact on sponsorship deals, merchandising and shirt sales.
The club expects an increase of at least 30 percent in turnover due to the signing of the contract.
The Spanish league, clearly upset by the departure of one of the biggest football stars, tried to block Neymar’s move by claiming that PSG was violating FFP.
"This is a clear case of 'financial doping' with the club and the country," La Liga president Javier Tebas told Spanish newspaper AS, referring to PSG's ownership of Qatar.
Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger, whose club is owned by the American sports magnate, shares La Liga’s view that the club is financed by the state.
