Linda’s husband saw the garden he planted collapse.
What do you do with your hands when you’re facing a storm like this?
The sea came under the window, water splashed in through the windows," said Mrs Linda, who lived on Kalda Street in Haapsalu at the time.
That the roads were full of trees and the roof of the railway station platform had flown from 20 to 30 metres away, Linda, like most of the Haapsalus, could not see until the next morning.
According to locals, the trees behind Paralepa were at a low level, some completely lying down, some half down.
Everything looked very depressing, the storm passed through the beautiful old trees with ragged and crackling like a war.
