Haapsalu Castle Park and Padise Park were wiped off the face of the earth, but the parks around us were also severely damaged.
Wind speeds in Tallinn were measured at up to 35 metres per second, i.e. about 130 kilometres per hour.
On the evening of the 6th of August, a little girl in Merivälja, Tallinn, had shouted: "Mom, Mom!
The chickens are in the air and can't get down anymore!" wrote Virumaa Teataja.
The P<0xC3><0xB5>lli manor building in Viljandi County was so destroyed during the storm that it was decided to demolish it later.
The constructions of the T<0xC3><0xBC>ri ski jumping hill, which was later not restored, could not withstand the August storm.
